A: You are adding the first child's value to the list in every iteration of your loop. You should add the value of the current dataSnapshot1 to the list.
Replace this line:
names.add(dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator().next().getValue(String.class));

with this line:
names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));

So your updated code will be:
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        names.clear(); // clear the list before adding new values
        for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This should solve your problem.

A: You are using the iterator inside the loop which is not correct. You should use the iterator outside the loop and then use next() inside the loop to get the values.
Here is the correct code:
Iterator<DataSnapshot> dataSnapshotIterator = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator();
while(dataSnapshotIterator.hasNext()){
    DataSnapshot ds = dataSnapshotIterator.next();
    names.add(ds.getValue(String.class));
}

This way you are using the same iterator outside the loop and inside the loop you are using next() to get the values.

A: You are using the same iterator in each loop iteration. You should create a new iterator for each loop iteration.
Here is the correct code:
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        names.clear(); // clear the list before adding new values
        for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This way, you are creating a new iterator for each child in the dataSnapshot, and you are using the next() method to get the value of each child.

